FBIS3-28290 "dreas025__a94002" FBIS-EAS-94-025-A Document Type:Daily Report 7 February 1994 ANNEX Japan `Little Impact' of U.S. Monetary Policy Viewed OW0702125294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 6 Feb 94 Morning Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0702125294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] A senior official of the Bank of Japan, in connection with U.S. decision on 4 February to implement a tighter monetary policy, believes that "it is a precautionary measure against inflation and will have little impact on Japanese economy, since chances are slim that long- and short-term interest rates in the United States will rise rapidly." He, therefore, maintains that "Japanese monetary policies will not be affected."
